@startuml
title Viaverse Chat / Messaging / Safety — Component Diagram

component "KMP Client\nchat UI\nattachments\nreceipts" as Client
component "Realtime BFF\nWebSocket/SSE/polling\nsession binding" as BFF
component "ChatController\nConversationController\nReceiptController" as Controller
component "Chat Use Cases\nOpenConversation\nSendMessage\nUpdateReceipt\nReportMessage\nExportForDispute" as UseCases
component "Chat Policies\nparticipant access\njob state\nPII/off-platform safety\nretention" as Policies
component "Ports\nMessageRepo\nMarketplacePort\nSafetyPort\nMediaPort\nNotificationPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "marketplace-service\njob/order context\nparticipants" as Market
component "safety/moderation-service\ntext/media scan\nreport queue" as Safety
component "media-service\nattachments\nsigned access" as Media
database "Cassandra\nmessages\nreceipts\nconversation timeline" as Cassandra
database "PostgreSQL\nconversation metadata\nreports\npolicy state" as PG
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nMessageSent\nMessageReported\nConversationArchived" as Kafka

Client --> BFF : realtime/HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : command/query
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> Market : participant/job state
Ports --> Safety : scan/report
Ports --> Media : attachment refs
Ports --> Cassandra : message timeline
Ports --> PG : metadata/reports
UseCases --> Kafka : events

note bottom
Use Cassandra for high-volume message timeline/read receipts,
PostgreSQL for conversation metadata/reports/policies.
Keep attachments as mediaId refs, not binary in chat DB.
end note
@enduml
